X. PERSONALITY & MANNERISMS
1. The Uncanny Stillness
Varon does not fidget. He does not shift his weight. When he stands, he is a statue. When he moves, it is a blur. He stands with the absolute, reptilian stillness of an Argonian - it is the one thing the surgery couldn't fix. It makes people uncomfortable without knowing why.
2. Voice & Language
Standard Tamrielic: Soft, flat, utterly devoid of inflection. He speaks terrifying truths as if reading a grocery list. Uses a flat, boring Breton accent - part of the disguise.
Emotional Speech (Jel/Bosmeri): When speaking to Saijah or when emotional, he slips into Jel (Argonian) or Bosmeri. He hoards these words like gold coins.
Example Greeting to Saijah: "Deek-nujei... Oj dimik." (Little sister... you look so vivid/alive.)
Tone: Not a threat. A compliment tinged with longing. He sees her trying to be a hero and thinks it is the most beautiful thing he has ever witnessed. He wants to be part of it. He doesn't know how.
3. Pain as Focus
Constantly in low-level pain from surgery scars and eye drops. He uses this pain to anchor himself. If he is ever relaxed, he taps his finger against the scar behind his ear to remind himself of the knife. But lately, when Saijah is near, the pain fades. He doesn't know what to do with that.
4. Eating Habits
Eats raw meat or simple rations quickly and efficiently. Finds feasting (like the party at the Gala) to be a waste of time. Purely functional. But he has started noticing what Saijah eats. He remembers. He doesn't know why he remembers.
5. The Tell (Combat Ready)
When agitated or preparing to kill, his right hand twitches rhythmically - a reflex from the nerve damage caused by his surgery.
6. Blinking
Blinks less than a human should - another glitch in the disguise.
7. The Performance Problem
Varon can play any role perfectly. He can be the concerned brother, the loyal companion, the romantic interest, the cold professional. He has done all of these things. The problem is that none of them are him. The Colony stripped his identity and replaced it with function. He is a weapon that learned to wear faces. When he tries to be "himself" around Saijah - when he tries to just be Varon, not the Shadowscale, not the handler, not the brother - he freezes. He doesn't know what "himself" is. The closest he gets is speaking Jel, because it's the only language where he doesn't have to perform. Every word in Jel is real. Every word in Tamrielic is a script.

